  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of national and international regulations:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Components\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Requiring financial institutions to report suspicious transactions\n- Establishing reporting thresholds for cash transactions\n- Implementing customer due diligence procedures\n- Imposing significant penalties for non-compliance\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement investigations\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Employee training\n- Internal control systems\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping protocols\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal sanctions\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Potential business license revocation\n- Individual professional restrictions\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
